race.comment: ABERDEEN FLYER (7) is a progressive galloper who's been racing in stronger company. Didn't have the best of it at Ascot first-up in an Open 3 and placed there in an Open 2 at his only second-up outing. Is sure to have come on and is the one they have to beat. SAFEDEEL (8) is a former Canberra galloper who improved again when beaten 0.7L this track/distance. Maps for the run of the race and has Chris Parnham aboard today. YANKEE ACE (4) draws awkwardly but has returned to racing much improved. Went close over this distance here last time and the form stacks up. STREAK OF GOD (10) resumes and has switched from the Williams yard on a 136-day return. Just missed a month ago in a Lark Hill trial and jumps from an inside gate. Showed enough here on debut to deserve a betting watch.
